-- EBay profit rises; Icahn proposes spin-off of PayPal
-- By Phil Wahba in New York
-- Wed Jan 22, 2014 04:27PM EST
-- None



Jan 22 (Reuters) - EBay Inc <EBAY.O> on Wednesday reported a higher profit for the holiday quarter as more transactions were paid with its PayPal service.

The e-commerce company also said activist investor Carl Icahn submitted a proposal to spin off eBay's PayPal business. Net income for the fourth quarter, which included the holiday season, was $850 million, or 65 cents a share, up from $751 million, or 57 cents a share, a year earlier. Excluding some items, eBay earned 81 cents per share.